title: UMD's Brees Earns NSIC Weekly Honor
text:
UMD's Brees Earns NSIC Weekly Honor 
By Zach Schneider UMD's Brees Earns NSIC Weekly Honor October 19, 2015 Updated Oct 19, 2015 at 1:16 PM CDT 
Duluth, MN (NNCNOW.com) --- University of Minnesota Duluth (UMD) senior placekicker Andrew Brees has been named the Northern Sun Intercollegiate Conference (NSIC) special teams player of the week, it was announced on Monday afternoon. 
Brees set a school record this past Saturday with a 57-yard field goal, and he was also 6-for-6 on extra points.
